Tokyo stocks end down on weak brokerages , builders . Tokyo stocks closed moderately lower on Friday , mainly depressed by continuing weakness in the brokerage and construction sectors , brokers said . A downturn on Wall Street overnight also clouded sentiment , with many dealers squaring positions ahead of key U . S . employment data due out later in the day , they said . But the downside is seen as limited , as some blue chips have attracted investors , backed by good earnings forecasts . The 225 - share Nikkei average lost 268 . 72 points or 1 . 48 percent to close at 17 , 860 . 59 . Its June futures gave up 230 points to 17 , 850 . 
